---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Child Custody Attorney Maryland | Divorce With A Plan"
  description="Maryland child custody attorneys serving Rockville, Baltimore, and Montgomery County. Legal & physical custody, parenting plans, and Best Interest Attorney representation. Free consultation."
  ogTitle="Child Custody Attorney Maryland | Divorce With A Plan"
  ogDescription="Experienced Maryland child custody attorneys. We protect your parental rights and your children's best interests. Certified Best Interest Attorneys on staff."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-900 to-slate-700 text-white py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto text-center">
      <p class="text-amber-400 uppercase tracking-widest text-sm font-semibold mb-3">Maryland Child Custody Attorneys</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6 leading-tight">
        Protecting Your Children.<br class="hidden md:block" />
        Securing Your Parental Rights.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-slate-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-8">
        Child custody is the most emotionally charged aspect of any divorce or separation. Our Maryland family law attorneys fight for parenting arrangements that truly serve your children's best interests — and protect your rights as a parent.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/free-consultation" class="bg-amber-500 hover:bg-amber-600 text-white font-bold py-3 px-8 rounded-lg transition-colors">
          Schedule Free Consultation
        </a>
        <a href="tel:2402693592" class="border-2 border-white hover:bg-white hover:text-slate-900 text-white font-bold py-3 px-8 rounded-lg transition-colors">
          Call (240) 269-3592
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Types of Custody -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Understanding Custody in Maryland</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Maryland recognizes two distinct types of custody — legal and physical — each of which can be sole or shared.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Legal Custody</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-4">
            Legal custody refers to the right and responsibility to make major decisions about your child's life — including decisions about <strong>education, medical care, religious upbringing, and extracurricular activities</strong>.
          </p>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4 border border-slate-200">
              <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-sm mb-1">Sole Legal Custody</h4>
              <p class="text-slate-600 text-xs">One parent has the exclusive right to make major decisions. The other parent may have visitation but no decision-making authority.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4 border border-slate-200">
              <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-sm mb-1">Shared Legal Custody</h4>
              <p class="text-slate-600 text-xs">Both parents share decision-making responsibility and must consult with each other on major decisions. Most common outcome in Maryland.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Physical Custody</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-4">
            Physical custody determines where the child primarily lives and which parent is responsible for day-to-day care during each parent's custodial time.
          </p>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4 border border-slate-200">
              <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-sm mb-1">Sole Physical Custody</h4>
              <p class="text-slate-600 text-xs">The child lives primarily with one parent. The other parent typically has scheduled visitation (access) time.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4 border border-slate-200">
              <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-sm mb-1">Shared Physical Custody</h4>
              <p class="text-slate-600 text-xs">The child spends significant time in both parents' homes. Often a more equal time-sharing arrangement.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Best Interests Standard -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-slate-50">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-5">The "Best Interests of the Child" Standard</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
            In Maryland, all custody decisions are governed by the <strong>"best interests of the child"</strong> standard. Courts do not automatically favor one parent over the other — they evaluate a comprehensive set of factors to determine what arrangement will best serve the child.
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
            Understanding how these factors apply to your specific situation — and how to present them persuasively to the court — is where experienced legal representation makes all the difference.
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            Our attorneys, including two <strong>Certified Best Interest Attorneys</strong> (Josephia Rouse and Massa Massaquoi-King), have deep expertise in how Maryland courts evaluate custody cases.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Factors Courts Evaluate</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            {[
              "Fitness of each parent",
              "Character and reputation of each parent",
              "Material opportunities available to the child",
              "Age, health, and sex of the child",
              "Residences of parents and proximity to each other",
              "Length of any separation",
              "Prior voluntary abandonment or surrender of custody",
              "The child's preference (when age-appropriate)",
              "Each parent's ability to communicate and reach shared decisions",
              "Each parent's willingness to share custody",
              "History of domestic violence or abuse",
              "Relationship between the child and each parent"
            ].map(factor => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-500 font-bold mt-0.5">✓</span>
                <span class="text-slate-700 text-sm">{factor}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Certified Best Interest Attorney -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-12">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-center">
          <div>
            <p class="text-amber-600 font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-sm mb-3">Distinguished Credential</p>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Certified Best Interest Attorneys on Our Team</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
              In Maryland, a <strong>Best Interest Attorney (BIA)</strong> is a specially trained and certified attorney appointed by the court to represent a child's interests in custody proceedings — entirely separate from both parents' attorneys.
            </p>
            <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
              Both <strong>Josephia Rouse</strong> (Founder) and <strong>Massa Massaquoi-King</strong> (Managing Attorney) hold BIA certifications — a rare credential that demonstrates exceptional expertise in child advocacy and Maryland family court proceedings.
            </p>
            <p class="text-slate-600">
              This experience gives our team unique insight into how courts evaluate custody cases and what truly serves children's interests — making us more effective advocates for our clients.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">What a BIA Does</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3">
              {[
                "Conducts independent investigation of the child's circumstances",
                "Interviews the child (age-appropriate)",
                "Interviews parents, teachers, and other key individuals",
                "Reviews medical, school, and other relevant records",
                "Makes recommendations to the court based solely on the child's welfare",
                "Can call witnesses and cross-examine at hearings"
              ].map(item => (
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
                  <span class="text-amber-500 mt-0.5">•</span>
                  <span>{item}</span>
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Parenting Plans -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-slate-50">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Building a Strong Parenting Plan</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">A well-drafted parenting plan eliminates ambiguity and reduces future conflict. We help you create a comprehensive, detailed plan tailored to your family's needs.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {[
          { title: "Regular Schedule", desc: "Day-to-day schedule specifying where the child will be on each day of the week and during school hours." },
          { title: "Holiday & Vacation Schedule", desc: "Clear allocation of major holidays, school breaks, and family vacations to avoid seasonal conflicts." },
          { title: "School & Education Decisions", desc: "How decisions about school enrollment, tutoring, extracurricular activities, and educational needs will be made." },
          { title: "Medical Decision-Making", desc: "How routine and emergency medical decisions will be handled, and how each parent will be notified." },
          { title: "Communication Protocols", desc: "How parents will communicate with each other and how the child will communicate with each parent during custodial time." },
          { title: "Relocation Provisions", desc: "Rules governing if and when a parent can relocate with or without the child, including notice requirements." }
        ].map(item => (
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">{item.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">{item.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Special Situations -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-slate-900 text-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Complex Custody Situations We Handle</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        {[
          { title: "High-Conflict Custody", desc: "When communication between parents breaks down completely, we provide strategic representation to protect your interests and your children." },
          { title: "Relocation Cases", desc: "If one parent wants to move with the children, the stakes are high. We handle both sides of relocation disputes in Maryland." },
          { title: "Domestic Violence Cases", desc: "We protect clients and children facing safety concerns, pursuing protective orders and custody arrangements that ensure safety." },
          { title: "De Facto & Third-Party Custody", desc: "Managing Attorney Massa Massaquoi-King fiercely advocates in de facto and third-party custody cases — a complex area of Maryland family law." }
        ].map(item => (
          <div class="bg-slate-800 rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-amber-400 mb-3">{item.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm">{item.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-amber-500">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Your Children's Future Matters. Let's Protect It Together.</h2>
      <p class="text-amber-100 mb-8 text-lg">Schedule a free consultation with our Maryland child custody attorneys today.</p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/free-consultation" class="bg-white text-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-50 font-bold py-3 px-8 rounded-lg transition-colors">
          Book Free Consultation
        </a>
        <a href="tel:2402693592" class="border-2 border-white text-white hover:bg-amber-600 font-bold py-3 px-8 rounded-lg transition-colors">
          (240) 269-3592
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
